  RELEVANCE: Provides alternative to extended mind debates by reframing questions about cognitive boundaries. Instead of asking whether external resources constitute cognition, cognitive ecology asks how cognitive systems emerge from interactions across multiple components and timescales. This framework offers different lens for interpreting offloading phenomena as ecosystem-level processes.

